    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong>, then zest <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) and grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> in 75ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a small bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then heat in the<strong> microwave </strong>for 20-30 secs until melted and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy lemon garlic drizzle</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt and rinse under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool, then once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can and chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken breast strips </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> tortiglioni </strong>for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy</strong> <strong>pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once your chicken is golden, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>with the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for a further 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked chicken </strong>to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong>, your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then add a splash of <strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>(add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken & tomato tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>zested lemon[s]</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-and-tomato-tortiglioni-with-spicy-lemon-garlic-drizzle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> chicken & tomato tortiglioni </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and the<strong> spicy lemon garlic drizzle</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the spicy lemon garlic drizzle and just sprinkle over some grated cheese!</span></strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>and taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
